      </div>

      <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-6" data-markdown>
I'm currently out of work, but expecting to get started full-time in the near future<sup><a href="#footnote-3">[3]</a></sup>. In the meantime, I'm very much into [open source projects](https://github.com/majodev), contribute [here](https://github.com/cryptocat/cryptocat/pull/694) and [there](https://github.com/edjafarov/node-webkit-updater/issues/56) and work on some [small projects](http://majodev.github.io/sjgrabber). I love well documented, tested and maintainable code. At the very moment, my language of choice is JavaScript, but I've also had a hell of a time with AS3/Flex, PHP and Java *(and unfortunately VB)*.
      </div>

      <div class="col-md-offset-1 col-md-5 col-sm-6" data-markdown>
Beware, I'm not your future creative designer<sup><a href="#footnote-4">[4]</a></sup>, however I like to get involved in your whole development process. Abstracting and optimizing lies in my very nature. Data modeling, code decoupling, applying design patterns, tooling, testing and deploying is what I do and love.

      </div>

      <div class="col-md-5 col-sm-6" data-markdown>
Apart from my professional life, I have a weakness for weird music<sup><a href="#footnote-5">[5]</a></sup>, hot 'n' spicy food, beautiful beaches and indie or retro SNES games. Furthermore I play the guitar (mediocre) and the piano (poorly) and skim through tekkie / startup related articles everyday.
